The decomposing body of the missing daughter of Githongo Law Courts magistrate Caroline Keme has been found at Gitoro Forest in Imenti North, Meru county. The body of 9-year-old Marrybelle Kapolon, who was kidnapped on September 6, was discovered on Sunday night. The incident occurred as the girl was heading home from Consolata Primary School along Total road in Meru. Police said a member of the public, who found the body, informed the area assistant chief. The deceased was in her school uniform and one shoe was at the scene. DCI officers from Imenti North Division and police moved the body to Meru Level 5 Hospital mortuary awaiting an autopsy. Click here for the latest political news 